				<h2 class="tk-league-gothic">Buy Apps for Japan&nbsp;</h2>
				<h3 class="author"><em>by</em> Dirk Stoop</h3>
				<p class="intro">All of today's revenues will go to Japan, read on for details and please consider contributing.</p>
				<p>Buy now: <a href="http://www.versionsapp.com/buy">Versions</a>, <a href="http://www.kaleidoscopeapp.com/buy">Kaleidoscope</a>, <a href="http://www.checkoutapp.com/buy">Checkout</a>. </p>
				
			</div>
			<div class="right_col">
				<p>We were struck with horror when we heard about the earthquake and subsequent tsunami in Japan. Today, we're asking you to join us in trying to help. Together we can contribute to restoring normalcy, even if it's only a little bit.</p>

<p>Sofa will donate 100% of today's <a href="http://www.versionsapp.com">Versions</a> or <a href="http://www.kaleidoscopeapp.com">Kaleidoscope</a> sales to charity work in Japan (details below). And together with our partners at <a href="http://acclivitysoftware.com">Acclivity</a> and Checkout Australia, we are doing exactly the same for every copy of <a href="http://www.checkoutapp.com">Checkout</a>. Also see our <a href="http://checkoutapp.tumblr.com/post/4030194581/helping-japan">joint post</a> on the Checkout blog.</p>

<p>If you were thinking about getting any of our products, please do so before Thursday 9am GMT (or 4am in New York, 10am in Amsterdam) and 100% of your money will go toward helping people who lost their homes, loved ones, or were otherwise hurt in this disaster.</p>

<p>We will split the total between <a href="http://www.doctorswithoutborders.org/">Doctors Without Borders</a>, <a href="http://www.habitat.org/">Habitat for Humanity</a> and the <a href="http://www.jrc.or.jp/english/index.html">Japanese Red Cross</a>. Each is making a very tangible difference.</p>

<p>Kudos to our friends at <a href="http://www.panic.com/blog/2011/03/lets-help-japan/">Panic</a> and <a href="http://www.marketcircle.com/japan">Marketcircle</a> for inspiring us with their generous donations.</p>

<p>Please spread the word. The more people we can entice to donate, either by buying some of our software or otherwise, the better. Thanks from everyone at Sofa.</p>
